cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the analysis of a network of related blogs, which involves topics such as social networks, information retrieval, and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes an algorithm to detect fine-grained discussion topics, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). The analysis of the network involves studying the dynamics of topic participation, which is related to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The paper also mentions the possible application of the results to search engine ranking algorithms, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
